One of the new aspects in Middle-earth is player housing.  Now new and improved over previous version!

Just speak to any of the Real Estate agents to learn more.  There are three, one near Rivendell, one near Edoras and the third inside Minas Tirith.

0:10.description:8:
Real Estate agents in Middle-earth can help you find that perfect home if you just let them.  There are 3 to start out with, one near Rivendell, one near Edoras and the last inside Minas Tirith.  Speak to any one of them to learn more about player housing.

Server admins will be able to add more if needed using the template and deciding on houses.

Reach out to him, see what has transpired since last you two spoke.
Take the gem Lord Glorfindel bestowed upon you and see what you can find out.

Glóin told you that the Nazgûl you are pursuing can be found in the old dwarf-fortress of Gundabad, in the company of Dugorim Dourhand. The two entered the nearly impregnable inner keep of the fortress. Glóin believes the only way to enter the inner keep is to learn its secret entrance.
Glóin has asked you to retrieve a key-stone from an old dwarf-vault. The key-stone will allow you entry into the Dourhand-occupied dwarf-keep.

With the Key-stone found, you can now enter the dwarf-keep in Gundabad, the last refuge of the Dourhands and confront both the Nazgûl and Dugorim.

Gimli is located near the secret entrance to Gundabad, follow the compass in your journal to find him to gain entrance to Gundabad.
Upon hearing that the Nazgûl fled to Carn Dûm, Glóin told you some of the tale of that ancient fortress.

Near one of the entrances to Carn Dûm you encountered wights.

After killing a few you found a §5Dark Sigil§r so you should return to Glóin and see what he thinks.

The threat in Carn Dûm has been dealt with and now Elrond wants to discuss other matters with you.

Speak with him in Rivendell.

A trained falcon arrived at Rivendell, bearing a troubling message from the hidden Ranger-camp at Mitheithel for Aragorn, Chieftain of the Rangers.

Guthwine told you of how a wounded falcon arrived, bearing a message from Manwyn, a Ranger from the company of Cromhes, who defied Aragorn's commands and passed into Khazad-dûm, believing that a shadow had come again there.

Manwyn believes that the secret of of the Watchers can be revealed by investigating one of the pedestals they rest on. He has instructed you to carefully approach one of the Watchers and take a rubbing of the runes upon it. He warned you to be very careful of the fell and deadly Watchers.
The rubbing you made showed runes of a foul nature, written in the Black Speech, which Manwyn is not well-versed in; however, he was able to make out something about the "heart" of the stone.

While the stone-heart you found was cracked and useless, another path still remains open. Corunir has learned of a ritual taking place at the fortress of Dol Guldur, which may yield a whole heart if interrupted.

Manwyn bade you pass through the Watchers, for you no longer have cause to fear the deadly stones. He hopes that you may find a remnant of the force Cromhes led through the stones somewhere on the other side.
Manwyn believes the charm he placed on you will allow you passage through the Watchers, but warns that it may draw an Ancient spirit out you must defeat.

Manwyn bade you pass through the Watchers, for you no longer have cause to fear the deadly stones. He hopes that you may find a remnant of the force Cromes led through the stones somewhere on the other side.

You have been tasked with locating the other rangers deeper within Moria in the area known as the Flaming Deeps.
You found the camp and have spoken to Tonvid but he has bade you speak with Layles as the trouble at hand is personal for her.  She is in a nearby tent.
Apparently the rangers have sympathizers within the enemy ranks and one in particular, Fridli, has decided to help them with some potentially useful information.
You found Fridli and have obtained the scroll, time to take it back to Layles and see if it was worth the effort.
Since the scroll was written in a strange language, referred to as the black speech, Layles has asked you to reach out to Thurdan at the Caravan Camp near the entrance of the Flaming Deeps for help.
Thurdan has sent you to speak to Elrond who he says should have no trouble translating the scroll you found to unlock its secrets.

You have received a translated version of the scroll and Elrond has tasked you with going to speak to Lord Dáin II Ironfoot to see if his dwarves can create the key needed.
Bilbo apparently kept a souvenier from his early exploits and may have left it at home when he travelled to Rivendell not realizing what it truly was.
Derwyn, the Captain of the guard in Archet is said to have a key they found that may be just what we need to make a mould.
Time to retrieve the tool Elssuli needs to complete our task.
After some grueling tasks you have retrieved the key, time to return to Layles and see what's next.

30 years have passed since the forming of the council, Man, Dwarf and Elf.  They came together to try to stop the coming darkness in Angmar.  At the same time, you were trying to stop Draconis from destruction and to contain the evil that was spreading to the Overworld.

Sadly, one by one, the free peoples were defeated as the growing evil was stronger than anyone realized.  The last time you were here, Strider, now known as Aragorn had said something about the ring you had returned to Bilbo and Gandalf had been researching.

It will be up to you to help fight back this evil and see what can be done to help the Fellowship succeed in a new task.  Be strong traveler and know that if ever a Hero was needed, the Hero of Draconis shall be the one to answer that call!
